==Events==
* [[708]] &amp;ndash; Copper coins are minted in [[Japan]] for the first time (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: August 10, 708).
*[[1350]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Winchelsea]] (or [[Les Espagnols sur Mer]]): The [[England|English]] [[naval fleet]] under King [[Edward III of England|Edward III]] defeats a [[Crown of Castile|Castilian]] fleet of 40 ships.
*[[1475]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of Picquigny]] ends a brief war between [[France]] and England.
*[[1498]] &amp;ndash; [[Vasco da Gama]] decides to depart [[Calicut]] and return to [[Portugal]].
*[[1521]] &amp;ndash; The [[Ottoman Turks]] capture [[Nándorfehérvár]], now known as [[Belgrade]].
*[[1526]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Mohács]]: The [[Ottoman Turks]] led by [[Suleiman the Magnificent]] defeat and kill the last [[Jagiellonian]] king of [[Hungary]] and [[Bohemia]].
*[[1541]] &amp;ndash; The [[Ottoman Turks]] capture [[Buda]], the [[Capital (political)|capital]] of the [[Hungarian Kingdom]].
*[[1655]] &amp;ndash; [[Warsaw]] falls without resistance to a small force under the command of [[Charles X Gustav of Sweden]] during [[Deluge (history)|The Deluge]].
*[[1756]] &amp;ndash; [[Frederick the Great]] attacks [[Saxony]], beginning the [[Seven Years' War]].
*[[1758]] &amp;ndash; The first American [[Indian Reservation]] is established, at Indian Mills, New Jersey.
*[[1786]] &amp;ndash; [[Shays' Rebellion]], an armed uprising of [[Massachusetts]] farmers, begins in response to high debt and tax burdens.
*[[1825]] &amp;ndash; [[Portugal]] recognizes the Independence of [[Brazil]].
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; [[Michael Faraday]] discovers [[electromagnetic induction]].
*[[1833]] &amp;ndash; The [[United Kingdom]] legislates the abolition of [[slavery]] in its empire.
*[[1842]] &amp;ndash; [[Treaty of Nanking]] signing ends the [[First Opium War]].
*[[1861]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[US Navy]] squadron captures forts at Hatteras Inlet, [[North Carolina]].
*[[1869]] &amp;ndash; The [[Mount Washington Cog Railway]] opens, making it the world's first [[rack railway]].
*[[1871]] &amp;ndash; [[Emperor Meiji]] orders the [[Abolition of the han system]] and the establishment of [[Prefectures of Japan|prefectures]] as local centers of administration. (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: July 14, 1871).
*[[1885]] &amp;ndash; [[Gottlieb Daimler]] patents the world's first [[internal combustion]] [[motorcycle]], the [[Daimler Reitwagen|''Reitwagen'']]
*[[1898]] &amp;ndash; The [[Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company|Goodyear]] tire company is founded.
*[[1903]] &amp;ndash; The [[Russian battleship Slava|Russian battleship ''Slava'']], the last of the five {{Sclass|Borodino|battleship}}s, is launched.
*[[1907]] &amp;ndash; The [[Quebec Bridge]] collapses during construction, killing 75 workers.
*[[1910]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan]] changes [[Korea]]'s name to ''Chōsen'' and appoints a [[governor-general]] to rule its new [[colony]].
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; [[Ishi]], considered the last [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]] to make contact with [[European Americans]], emerges from the wilderness of northeastern [[California]].
*[[1915]] &amp;ndash; [[US Navy]] salvage divers raise [[USS F-4 (SS-23)|F-4]], the first U.S. [[submarine]] sunk in accident.
*[[1916]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States]] passes the [[Jones Law (Philippines)|Philippine Autonomy Act]].
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[Bapaume]] taken by the [[New Zealand Division]] in the [[Hundred Days Offensive]]
*[[1922]] &amp;ndash; [[Turkey|Turkish]] forces set [[Great Fire of Smyrna|fire]] to [[Smyrna]] in [[Asia Minor]].
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; The last 36 remaining inhabitants of [[St Kilda, Scotland|St Kilda]] are voluntarily evacuated to other parts of [[Scotland]].
*[[1943]] &amp;ndash; [[Occupation of Denmark|German-occupied Denmark]] scuttles most of its [[navy]]; [[Germany]] dissolves the [[Denmark|Danish]] government.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[Slovak National Uprising]] takes place as 60,000 [[Slovaks|Slovak]] troops turn against the [[Nazism|Nazi]]s.
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; [[Soviet atomic bomb project]]: The [[Soviet Union]] tests its first [[atomic bomb]], known as ''[[First Lightning]]'' or ''Joe 1'', at [[Semipalatinsk Test Site|Semipalatinsk]], [[Kazakhstan]].
*[[1958]] &amp;ndash; [[United States Air Force Academy]] opens in [[Colorado Springs, Colorado]].
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[The Beatles]] perform their last concert before paying fans at [[Candlestick Park]] in [[San Francisco]].
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; [[Chicano Moratorium]] against the [[Vietnam War]], [[East Los Angeles, California]]. Police riot kills three people, including journalist [[Ruben Salazar]].
*[[1982]] &amp;ndash; The synthetic [[chemical element]] [[Meitnerium]], [[atomic number]] 109, is first synthesized at the [[Gesellschaft für Schwerionenforschung]] in [[Darmstadt]], [[Germany]].
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Supreme Soviet of the Soviet Union]] suspends all activities of the [[Soviet Communist Party]].
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Libero Grassi]], an Italian businessman from [[Palermo]] is killed by the [[Mafia]] after taking a solitary stand against their [[extortion]] demands.
*[[1996]] &amp;ndash; [[Vnukovo Airlines Flight 2801]], a Vnukovo Airlines [[Tupolev Tu-154]], crashes into a mountain on the [[Arctic]] island of [[Spitsbergen]], killing all 141 aboard.
*[[1997]] &amp;ndash; At least 98 villagers are killed by the Armed Islamic Group of Algeria [[Armed Islamic Group|GIA]] in the [[Rais massacre]], [[Algeria]].
*[[2003]] &amp;ndash; [[Ayatollah]] [[Sayed Mohammed Baqir al-Hakim]], the [[Shia Muslim]] leader in [[Iraq]], is [[assassination|assassin]]ated in a [[terrorism|terrorist]] bombing, along with nearly 100 worshippers as they leave a [[mosque]] in [[Najaf]].
*[[2005]] &amp;ndash; [[Hurricane Katrina]] [[Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans|devastates]] much of the [[U.S. Gulf Coast]] from [[Louisiana]] to the [[Florida Panhandle]], killing more than 1,836 and causing over $80 billion in damage.
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[2007 United States Air Force nuclear weapons incident]]: six US cruise missiles armed with nuclear warheads are flown without proper authorization from [[Minot Air Force Base]] to [[Barksdale Air Force Base]].

