{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1363]] &amp;ndash; Beginning date of the [[Battle of Lake Poyang]]; the forces of two [[China|Chinese]] rebel leaders — [[Chen Youliang]] and [[Zhu Yuanzhang]] — are pitted against each other in what is one of the [[Largest naval battle in history|largest naval battles in history]], during the last decade of the ailing, [[Mongol]]-led [[Yuan Dynasty]].
*[[1574]] &amp;ndash; [[Guru Ram Das]] becomes the Fourth [[Sikh Guru]]/[[guru|Master]].
*[[1590]] &amp;ndash; [[Tokugawa Ieyasu]] enters [[Edo Castle]]. (Traditional [[Japanese calendar|Japanese date]]: August 1, 1590)
*[[1791]] &amp;ndash; {{HMS|Pandora|1779|6}} sinks after having run aground on a reef the previous day.
*[[1799]] &amp;ndash; The entire [[Netherlands|Dutch]] fleet is captured by [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] forces under the command of [[Ralph Abercromby|Sir Ralph Abercromby]] and [[Admiral]] [[Charles Mitchell|Sir Charles Mitchell]] during the [[Second Coalition]] of the [[French Revolutionary Wars]].
*[[1800]] &amp;ndash; [[Gabriel Prosser]] leads a [[slave rebellion]] in [[Richmond, Virginia|Richmond]], [[Virginia]]
*[[1813]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Kulm]]: [[France|French]] forces are defeated by an [[Austria]]n-[[Prussia]]n-[[Russia]]n alliance.
*  1813   &amp;ndash; [[Creek War]] &amp;ndash; [[Fort Mims massacre]]: [[Creek people|Creek]] &quot;[[Red Sticks]]&quot; kill over 500 settlers (including over 250 armed militia) in Fort Mims, north of [[Mobile, Alabama]].
*[[1835]] &amp;ndash; [[Melbourne, Australia|Melbourne]], [[Australia]] is founded.
*[[1836]] &amp;ndash; The city of [[Houston, Texas|Houston]] is founded by [[Augustus Chapman Allen]] and [[John Kirby Allen]]
*[[1862]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Richmond]]: [[Confederate States of America|Confederates]] under [[Edmund Kirby Smith]] rout [[Union Army|Union]] forces under [[General]] [[Horatio Wright]].
*[[1873]] &amp;ndash; [[Austria]]n explorers [[Julius von Payer]] and [[Karl Weyprecht]] discover the [[archipelago]] of [[Franz Joseph Land]] in the [[Arctic Sea]].
*[[1897]] &amp;ndash; The town of [[Ambiky]] is captured by [[France]] from [[Menabe]] in [[Madagascar]].
*[[1896]] &amp;ndash; Eight provinces in the [[Philippines]] are declared under martial law by the Spanish [[Governor-General of the Philippines|Governor-General]] [[Ramón Blanco y Erenas]]. These are [[Manila]], [[Cavite]], [[Bulacan]], [[Pampanga]], [[Nueva Ecija]], [[Bataan]], [[Laguna (province)|Laguna]], and [[Batangas]].
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; [[Burgess Shale]] fossils are discovered by [[Charles Doolittle Walcott]].
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Tannenberg (1914)|Battle of Tannenberg]] is fought.
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[Fanny Kaplan]] shoots and seriously injures [[Bolshevik]] leader [[Vladimir Lenin]]. This, along with the assassination of [[Bolshevik]] senior official [[Moisei Uritsky]] days earlier, prompts the decree for [[Red Terror]].
*[[1922]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Dumlupinar]]: the final battle in the [[Greco-Turkish War (1919-1922)|Greek-Turkish War]] (&quot;Turkish War of Independence&quot;).
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; The [[Second Vienna Award]] re-assigns the territory of [[Northern Transylvania]] from [[Romania]] to [[Hungary]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; World War II: the [[Battle of Alam Halfa]] begins.
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; [[Hong Kong]] is liberated from [[Japan]] by [[British Armed Forces]].
*  1945   &amp;ndash; The [[Commander-in-Chief#United States|Supreme Commander]] of the Allied Forces, [[Douglas MacArthur|General Douglas MacArthur]] lands at [[NAF Atsugi|Atsugi Air Force Base]].
*[[1956]] &amp;ndash; The [[Lake Pontchartrain Causeway]] opens.
*[[1962]] &amp;ndash; [[Japan]] conducts a test of the [[NAMC YS-11]], its first aircraft since [[World War II]] and its only successful commercial aircraft from before or after the war.
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; The [[Moscow-Washington hotline|Hotline]] between the leaders of the [[United States|U.S.A.]] and the [[Soviet Union]] goes into operation.
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; [[Thurgood Marshall]] is confirmed as the first [[African American]] [[Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States|Justice]] of the [[Supreme Court of the United States]].
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; A [[Belgrade]]–[[Dortmund]] express train derails at the main train station in [[Zagreb]] killing 153 passengers.
*  1974   &amp;ndash; A powerful bomb explodes at the [[Mitsubishi Heavy Industries]] headquarters in [[Marunouchi]], [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]. 8 are killed, 378 are injured. Eight left-wing activists are arrested on May 19, 1975 by Japanese authorities.
*[[1984]] &amp;ndash; [[STS-41-D]]: The [[Space Shuttle]] ''[[Space Shuttle Discovery|Discovery]]'' takes off on its maiden voyage.
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; [[NATO]] launches [[Operation Deliberate Force]] against [[Bosnian Serb]] forces.

==Births==
