==Deaths==
* [[526]] &amp;ndash; [[Theodoric the Great]], King of the Ostrogoths and ruler of Italy (b. 454)
*[[1158]] &amp;ndash; King [[Sancho III of Castile]] (b. 1134)
*[[1329]] &amp;ndash; [[Khutughtu Khan, Emperor Mingzong of Yuan]], emperor of the Yuan Dynasty and the Mongol Empire (b. 1300)
*[[1428]] &amp;ndash; [[Emperor Shōkō]] of Japan (b. 1401)
*[[1483]] &amp;ndash; King [[Louis XI of France]] (b. 1423)
*[[1580]] &amp;ndash; [[Emmanuel Philibert, Duke of Savoy]] (b. 1528)
*[[1619]] &amp;ndash; [[Shimazu Yoshihiro]], Japanese samurai and warlord (b. 1535)
*[[1751]] &amp;ndash; [[Christopher Polhem]], Swedish scientist and inventor (b. 1661)
*[[1856]] &amp;ndash; [[Gilbert Abbott à Beckett]], English writer (b. 1811)
*[[1879]] &amp;ndash; [[John Bell Hood]], American Confederate general (b. 1831)
*[[1886]] &amp;ndash; [[Ferris Jacobs, Jr.]], American politician (b. 1836)
*[[1896]] &amp;ndash; [[Alexei Lobanov-Rostovsky]], Russian statesman (b. 1824)
*[[1906]] &amp;ndash; [[Hans Auer]], Swiss architect (b. 1847)
*[[1907]] &amp;ndash; [[Richard Mansfield]], American actor and manager (b. 1857)
*[[1928]] &amp;ndash; [[Wilhelm Wien]], German physicist, [[Nobel Prize in Physics|Nobel laureate]] (b. 1864)
